WHAT IS TRAINING, TESTING AND SPLITTING IN ML?
----->
In machine learning, training, testing, and splitting refer to how you handle your data to develop and evaluate your models effectively. Here's a breakdown of these concepts:

Training Data
Training: This is the process where the machine learning algorithm learns from the data. You feed the training data into the algorithm, and it adjusts its parameters to learn the patterns and relationships within the data. This set includes both the features (input variables) and the labels (output/target variable).
Testing Data
Testing: After training the model, you need to evaluate its performance to see how well it generalizes to new, unseen data. This is done using the testing data, which the model has never seen before. The performance on the testing data gives you an indication of how well the model will perform in real-world scenarios.
Data Splitting
Splitting: To create training and testing datasets, you split your original dataset into two parts. A common split ratio is 80-20, where 80% of the data is used for training, and 20% is used for testing. Sometimes, a 70-30 or 90-10 split might be used, depending on the size of the dataset and the specific needs of the problem.
Here's a more detailed step-by-step process of data splitting:

Initial Dataset: Start with your complete dataset containing both features and labels.
Shuffle the Data: Randomly shuffle the dataset to ensure that the data points are randomly distributed. This helps in avoiding any bias that might be present due to the ordering of the data.
Split the Data: Divide the dataset into two subsets:
Training Set: Used to train the model.
Testing Set: Used to evaluate the modelâ€™s performance.





WHAT IS LINEAR REGRESSION MODEL ?
---->
Linear regression is a fundamental and widely-used statistical method in machine learning for modeling the relationship between a dependent variable (target) and one or more independent variables (features). The key idea behind linear regression is to find the best-fitting straight line (in the case of simple linear regression) or hyperplane (in the case of multiple linear regression) that predicts the target variable based on the input features.




WHAT IS MULTIPLE REGRESSION MODEL ?
---->
A multiple regression model in machine learning is an extension of linear regression where the target variable is predicted based on multiple features. This type of regression is used when there are two or more independent variables (features) influencing the dependent variable (target).